{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Job Humbles Himself before the LORD"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And the LORD said to Job:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Will the faultfinder contend with the Almighty? Let him who argues with God give an answer.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then Job answered the LORD:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Behold, I am insignificant. How can I reply to You? I place my hand over my mouth.",
          "speaker": "Job"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "I have spoken once, but I have no answer—twice, but I have nothing to add.",
          "speaker": "Job"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "The LORD Challenges Job Again"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then the LORD answered Job out of the whirlwind and said:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "“Now brace yourself[^72] like a man; I will question you, and you shall inform Me.[^73]"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Would you really annul My justice? Would you condemn Me to justify yourself?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do you have an arm like God’s? Can you thunder with a voice like His?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then adorn yourself with majesty and splendor, and clothe yourself with honor and glory."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Unleash the fury of your wrath; look on every proud man and bring him low."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Look on every proud man and humble him; trample the wicked where they st and."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Bury them together in the dust; imprison them in the grave.[^74]"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then I will confess to youthat your own right hand can save you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Look at Behemoth, which I made along with you. He feeds on grass like an ox."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "See the strength of his loins and the power in the muscles of his belly."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "His tail sways like a cedar; the sinews of his thighs are tightly knit."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "His bones are tubes of bronze; his limbs are rods of iron."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He is the foremost of God’s works;[^75] only his Maker can draw the sword against him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The hills yield him their produce, while all the beasts of the field play nearby."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He lies under the lotus plants,[^76] hidden among the reeds of the marsh."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The lotus plants conceal him in their shade; the willows[^77] of the brook surround him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Though the river rages, Behemoth is unafraid; he remains secure, though the Jordan surges to his mouth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Can anyone capture him as he looks on, or pierce his nose with a snare?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}